primary_outcome.description:
MACCEs are defined by the Valve Academic Research Consortium (VARC-2) criteria.
MACCEs include the following device-related safety outcomes:
all-cause mortality including cardiovascular mortality;
all stroke (disabling and non-disabling);
bleeding (life-threatening or disabling);
acute kidney injury (stage 2 or 3 including new dialysis);
major device access related vascular complications;
coronary artery obstruction requiring intervention;
valve-related dysfunction requiring repeat procedure (balloon aortic valvuloplasty, repeat TAVI, or surgical aortic valve replacement)
